refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
boolimagegd2 GdImageimage stringnullfile&null; intchunk_size128 intmodeIMG_GD2_RAW
Outputs a GD2 image to the given file.

  &reftitle.parameters;



    &gd.image.description;

     file


&gd.image.path;



     chunk_size



       Chunk size.




     mode



       Either IMG_GD2_RAW or 
       IMG_GD2_COMPRESSED. Default is 
       IMG_GD2_RAW.

 &reftitle.examples;



   Outputting a GD2 image


<?php
// Create a blank image and add some text
$im = imagecreatetruecolor(120, 20);
$text_color = imagecolorallocate($im, 233, 14, 91);
imagestring($im, 1, 5, 5,  "A Simple Text String", $text_color);

// Output the image
imagegd2($im);
?>







    Saving a GD2 image


<?php
// Create a blank image and add some text
$im = imagecreatetruecolor(120, 20);
$text_color = imagecolorallocate($im, 233, 14, 91);
imagestring($im, 1, 5, 5,  "A Simple Text String", $text_color);

// Save the gd2 image
// The file format for GD2 images is .gd2, see http://www.libgd.org/GdFileFormats
imagegd2($im, 'simple.gd2');
?>

&reftitle.notes;



  The GD2 format is commonly used to allow fast loading of parts of images.
  Note that the GD2 format is only usable in GD2-compatible applications.


&gd.deprecated.gd-formats;
